32:14.224 --> 32:18.144
Maybe you should
start coming to see me
once a week for a while.

32:22.816 --> 32:25.192
Thanks, Miss Pillsbury.

32:25.277 --> 32:27.820
Don't forget your, um,
papers.

32:31.199 --> 32:33.618
[School Bell Rings]

32:33.702 --> 32:35.870
Guys, I've got good news.

32:35.954 --> 32:38.122
I siphoned off funds
from the Cheerios,

32:38.206 --> 32:41.125
and I took
a little shopping spree
through the Jazz Hands catalog.

32:41.209 --> 32:43.711
You know why?
'Cause the arts matter.

32:43.795 --> 32:49.383
And I got custom-made
New Directions jean jackets—

32:49.468 --> 32:51.844
Oh!

32:51.928 --> 32:54.305
and some rad
tear-away dance wear.

32:54.389 --> 32:58.476
Hello. And every piece
of sheet music...

32:58.560 --> 33:00.728
from every Broadway show
for the last 50 years—

33:00.812 --> 33:03.898
everything a show choir needs
to become champions.

33:03.982 --> 33:06.567
Wow. That's just amazing.
Let's all give a hand
for Mr. Ryan.

33:06.652 --> 33:10.112
Thank you.
Thank you.

33:10.197 --> 33:12.114
Congratulations, Will.

33:12.199 --> 33:14.116
I am over the moon
for you.

33:14.201 --> 33:16.827
Thanks, Sue. I'm glad
you have a good attitude
about your budget being cut.

33:16.912 --> 33:18.829
Oh, no, I'm not
talking about that.

33:18.914 --> 33:21.832
I came over here
to congratulate you
on your new role.

33:21.917 --> 33:25.670
Local director Herb Duncan,
uh, does the dry cleaning
for the Cheerios,

33:25.754 --> 33:30.549
and he let slip that you
just landed the lead
in Les Mis.

33:30.634 --> 33:34.261
Congratulations.
Oh, I'm ecstatic.

33:34.346 --> 33:37.682
And the good news
just keeps coming,
'cause you got a part too, Bry.

33:37.766 --> 33:40.685
The exciting role
of Townsperson.

33:40.769 --> 33:42.269
And you got a line too.

33:42.354 --> 33:46.148
Way back here
in the second act,
you get to say,

33:46.233 --> 33:48.109
"Hooray."

33:48.193 --> 33:49.819
Congratulations,
both of you, really.

33:49.903 --> 33:52.822
I can't wait
for opening night.

33:56.451 --> 33:58.577
[Exhales]

33:58.704 --> 34:00.705
[Chattering]
Wait, Bryan.

34:00.789 --> 34:03.332
Congratulations, Will.
You're gonna be great
in the show.

34:03.458 --> 34:07.086
Can we talk about this?
There's nothing to talk about.
I'm cutting the program.

34:10.507 --> 34:11.841
[Exhales]

34:14.010 --> 34:15.845
Hooray!

34:17.597 --> 34:19.265
Hooray.

34:19.391 --> 34:22.518
Hey, Bryan, can I talk
to you for a second?
Make it quick. I'm rehearsing.

34:22.602 --> 34:24.562
You know, reviewing
my single line.

34:24.646 --> 34:27.273
I want to take one last shot
at convincing you
not to cut the program.

34:27.357 --> 34:30.568
Give it a rest, Will.
You think you're
helping these kids,

34:30.652 --> 34:33.612
when all you're doing
is setting them up
to be jaded and bitter.

34:33.697 --> 34:35.614
You're right.
Cut the program,

34:35.699 --> 34:37.867
and they're
certainly more likely
to turn out like you.

34:39.494 --> 34:41.495
I've grown weary
of your insults, Will.

34:41.580 --> 34:45.332
They sting, and they make me
want to punch your face.

34:50.005 --> 34:55.134
You remember high school?
Remember what it's like?

34:55.218 --> 34:58.179
Those kids get labeled
the second they walk through
the door freshman year-

34:58.263 --> 35:02.558
geek, punk, jock, queer.

35:04.186 --> 35:06.520
I've seen who these kids
in Glee Club really are.

35:06.605 --> 35:10.566
No labels, no preconceptions.
Their true spirits.

35:12.152 --> 35:15.780
Yes, most of them
are not stars.

35:16.907 --> 35:19.742
But they shine like them.

35:19.826 --> 35:22.620
You know what happens
when a star dies, Bryan?

35:22.704 --> 35:25.456
It doesn't just disappear.
It turns into this black hole,

35:25.540 --> 35:28.667
this giant energy-sucking mass
that doesn’t just collapse in on itself.

35:28.752 --> 35:31.670
It takes away any light
that comes close down with it.

35:32.798 --> 35:35.299
If you take away Glee,

35:35.383 --> 35:38.511
you're not just putting out
those kids' lights.

35:38.595 --> 35:41.555
You're creating 13 black holes.

35:45.894 --> 35:47.812
[Sighs]

35:47.896 --> 35:49.897
I want you to take my part.

35:51.191 --> 35:54.401
You should play Jean Valjean.

36:00.200 --> 36:03.994
I want you to understand
how important the arts are
for a person's soul.

36:04.079 --> 36:06.205
You're a black hole right now.

36:06.289 --> 36:10.292
Maybe this will help you remember
what it's like to be a star.

36:10.377 --> 36:15.673
So what you're saying is
you'll give me the part...

36:15.757 --> 36:17.633
if I don't cut the program.

36:17.717 --> 36:19.593
Exactly.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.512
Cool. Deal.

36:21.596 --> 36:24.640
Oh, hey. Sir, hi.
I'm your new lead.

36:24.724 --> 36:27.059
And I'd just like to set up
some ground rules off the bat.

36:27.143 --> 36:29.353
First of all,
I have a lot of ideas.

36:29.437 --> 36:31.063
And next, I don't
really take direction.

36:34.776 --> 36:36.235
Jesse, what are you
doing here?

36:36.319 --> 36:38.696
I said that I was
going to help you
make your dreams come true.

36:38.780 --> 36:41.657
- No. I'm not ready.
- Yes, you are.

36:49.624 --> 36:53.961
♪♪ [Piano: Ballad]

36:54.045 --> 36:56.422
Hi, baby. It's your mom.

36:56.506 --> 36:59.925
I think this pretty much
says it all.

37:02.095 --> 37:07.766
♪ I dreamed a dream
in time gone by ♪

37:09.477 --> 37:14.815
♪ When hope was high
and life worth living ♪

37:16.192 --> 37:22.948
♪ I dreamed that love
would never die ♪

37:23.033 --> 37:29.663
♪ I dreamed that God
would be forgiving ♪

37:31.625 --> 37:38.422
♪ Then I was young
and unafraid ♪

37:38.506 --> 37:45.429
♪ And dreams were made
and used and wasted ♪

37:45.513 --> 37:52.436
♪ And there was no ransom
to be paid ♪

37:52.520 --> 37:59.234
♪ No song unsung
no wine untasted ♪

38:00.487 --> 38:03.280
♪ But the tigers
come at night ♪

38:03.365 --> 38:07.117
♪ But the tigers
come at night ♪

38:07.202 --> 38:13.749
♪ With their voices
soft as thunder ♪

38:13.833 --> 38:16.919
♪ As they tear
your hope apart ♪

38:17.003 --> 38:20.965
♪ As they tear
your hope apart ♪

38:21.049 --> 38:23.300
♪ As they turn
your dream ♪

38:23.385 --> 38:33.894
[Together]
♪ To shame ♪

38:35.021 --> 38:40.859
♪ And still I dream
she'll come to me ♪

38:40.944 --> 38:47.282
♪ That we will live
the years together ♪

38:47.367 --> 38:53.914
♪ But there are dreams
that cannot be ♪

38:53.999 --> 39:00.587
♪ And there are storms
we cannot weather ♪

39:03.967 --> 39:10.139
♪ I had a dream
my life would be ♪

39:10.223 --> 39:14.518
♪ So different from this hell
I'm living ♪

39:14.602 --> 39:20.441
♪ So different now
from what it seemed ♪

39:21.985 --> 39:28.282
[Together]
♪ Now life has
killed the dream ♪

39:29.534 --> 39:38.250
[Together]
♪ I dreamed ♪♪

39:49.637 --> 39:54.058
Artie, please think
about this.
I have.

39:54.142 --> 39:57.853
You've worked too hard
on this routine to have
half a partner.

39:57.937 --> 39:59.855
Fact is, any of the guys
in there...

39:59.939 --> 40:02.566
could dance my part
better than me
without even rehearsing.

40:02.692 --> 40:05.360
Well, except Finn.
But I wanna dance with you.

40:05.445 --> 40:08.781
I can't dance,
and I never will.

40:09.824 --> 40:12.242
But... that's okay.

40:12.327 --> 40:15.120
I'm never gonna
dunk a basketball
or kill a lion either.

40:16.664 --> 40:19.625
I have to focus on dreams
that I can make come true.

40:20.877 --> 40:23.796
I'm good, Tina.
Really.

40:30.845 --> 40:33.555
Will you at least
sing the song?

40:33.640 --> 40:35.557
Sure.

40:38.937 --> 40:40.437
[School Bell Rings]

40:40.522 --> 40:43.273
All right, guys.
Listen up.

40:43.358 --> 40:46.318
Tina has something
that she wants
to share with all of us.

40:46.402 --> 40:48.320
But first, I have
an announcement to make.

40:48.404 --> 40:50.823
You've all been reprieved.

40:50.907 --> 40:52.533
Bryan Ryan
isn't cutting Glee.

40:54.828 --> 40:58.080
- Did he die?
- No, he didn't die.

40:58.164 --> 41:00.374
He's gonna be distracted
for a couple months...

41:00.458 --> 41:03.377
making his star turn
in Les Mis.

41:03.461 --> 41:06.296
- He got the lead role.
- But I thought
you got the lead.

41:06.381 --> 41:09.550
I resigned.
It was the price
for keeping the Club.

41:09.634 --> 41:11.760
Sorry you had
to do that, Mr. Schue.

41:11.845 --> 41:13.387
I'm not.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.639
I mean, the-the way
I see it,

41:15.723 --> 41:18.058
I'm trading
my one dream...

41:18.143 --> 41:21.019
for the chance
that all 13 of you
might find yours.

41:21.104 --> 41:24.606
I mean, come on,
you can't argue
with those numbers.

41:24.691 --> 41:27.317
So, let's start
with Tina's dream.
Come on up, Tina.

41:27.402 --> 41:32.156
Tina, I understand
that you whipped up
a little dance number for us,

41:32.240 --> 41:34.283
a break-out that
we might use at regionals.

41:34.409 --> 41:37.202
Yes.
You got a dance partner?

41:39.455 --> 41:41.623
- Mike Chang.
- Chang!

41:41.708 --> 41:43.625
- [Will] Chang.
- [Boy] All right.

41:43.710 --> 41:46.128
[Girl]
Okay!

41:46.212 --> 41:46.879
♪♪ [Guitar, Pop Ballad]

41:46.880 --> 41:49.882
♪♪ [Guitar, Pop Ballad]

41:49.966 --> 41:55.470
♪ Stars shining bright
above you ♪

41:55.555 --> 42:00.142
♪ Night breezes seem
to whisper I love you ♪

42:00.226 --> 42:05.689
♪ Birds singing
in the sycamore tree ♪

42:05.773 --> 42:09.776
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

42:11.905 --> 42:16.617
♪ Say nighty-night
and kiss me ♪

42:16.701 --> 42:22.539
♪Just hold me tight
and tell me you'll miss me ♪

42:22.624 --> 42:27.085
♪ While I'm alone
and blue as can be ♪

42:27.170 --> 42:30.839
♪ Dream a little dream of me ♪

42:30.924 --> 42:33.550
[Chorus]
♪ Da, da, da
da, da, da ♪

42:33.635 --> 42:35.594
[Taps Clicking]

42:55.365 --> 43:00.327
♪ Sweet dreams
till sunbeams find you ♪

